  "body": "> This may have already been an issue (i.e. unrelated from your PR) but I noticed when I'm on a different network other than Mainnet (e.g. Arbitrum), it creates some funky behaviour when trying to connect (nothing happens when I click MetaMask). If I'm on Mainnet, it correctly tells me to switch to Goerli.\r\n\r\n> Mind making a change here to check if user is on ANY network other than the correct network? If so, we should display that modal to switch:\r\n<img width=\"583\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-05-30 at 9 33 47 AM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8097623/170940914-6134fcea-3b39-4be3-a834-c9ac4c88240e.png\">\r\n\r\n> ideal logic here might be to auto-switch the network for MetaMask users.\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @samajammin in https://github.com/ethereum/staking-launchpad/pull/495#pullrequestreview-988906310_",
